==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*widu-'', from Indo-European ''*widhu-''.  Cognate with Old High German [[witu]], Old Norse [[viðr]] (Swedish [[ved]]).  The IE root is also the source of Old irish [[fid]] (Welsh [[gwydd]], Breton [[gwez]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'wʊdʊ/

===Noun===
'''wudu''' ''m''
# a [[tree]]
# a [[wood]], [[woodland]]
# [[wood]] as a substance or material

